---
alwaysApply: true
---

Always use named Word styles (Heading 1, Heading 2, Heading 3, Normal)
when building documents via python-docx.
Never hardcode font names or sizes inline on paragraph runs.

Requirements must always be rendered as python-docx Table objects.
Never render requirements as plain text lists.

The LLM assigns sort_order only — never BRD IDs.
Assign IDs deterministically in code post-LLM: BRD-{MODULE}-{NNN}
(e.g., BRD-WO-001, BRD-INV-003), grouped by module, sorted by sort_order.

The DRAFT watermark must be implemented via XML injection into the
document header. Never use a text box or shape overlay.